SUBMISSIONS
We invite extended abstracts (maximum 1500 words) describing existing resea=
rch=20
connected to the topics of the workshop. Please note that as reviewing will=
=20
be blind, the abstract should not include the authors' names and=20
affiliations. Furthermore, self-references that reveal the author's identit=
y,=20
e.g., "We previously showed (Smith, 1991) ...", should be avoided. Instead,=
=20
use citations such as "Smith previously showed (Smith, 1991)...". Electroni=
c=20
submission (ps or pdf) is strongly encouraged.
Each submission should additionally include in the accompanying email: titl=
e;=20
author(s); affiliation(s); and contact author's e-mail address, postal=20
address, telephone and fax numbers.

    Abstracts should be sent to: mcivit@ub.edu clearly indicating in the=20
subject line: "TLT05 submission"

The presentation at the workshop will be 25 minutes long (20 minutes for=20
presentation and 5 minutes for questions and discussion). The final version=
=20
of the accepted papers may not exceed 12 A4 pages.

